reviewText: I love how the matheiral is put together- The sandbox sign up process is a bit confusing and if not done properly it can lead to issues with gaining access. I think one major improvement that will help with overall test and knowledge prep would be including the right answers with an explanination of why its right, rather than instructing us to go back and rewatch a video; if i didnt comprehened it once from how it was explained in that video then i need to learn at the moment of getting something wrong to correct myself, because im noticing im getting the same questions wrong.  this isnt just in this course. fix your platform.
The course is ok, but I have not received the advertised 50% voucher upon successful completion of the course. This is misleading, I will not trust Coursera ads anymore.

Although I have passed the AZ-900 exam, I found the actual exam had a very different format compared to what is in the course. I felt if I had not gone through other resources I may have not passed it. So please update the practise exams. The actual exams are harder.

I would not recommend paying specifically for this course. It is generally useful but the course needs to be updated to reflect the changes made by Microsoft to the AZ-900 exam in May 2022. The 50% discount for the exam is no longer available  (since over a year according to comments in the discussion forum). The same content is available for free (and up to date) on the Microsoft learn website.
N​o viene ningun tipo de temario, es solo para hacer los examenes

There were quite a number of mistakes in the content. The forums noted these mistakes but it doesn't appear anyone from Coursera or Microsoft is monitoring the forums. Since most of the content was the same as Microsoft Learn, I think it would be helpful to also share the relevant Microsoft Learn links along with the Coursera content. Also, it would be helpful if you showed the correct answers after quizes and exams are graded, or provide "more info" links for incorrect answers, where students can go to Microsoft documentation to learn more.
